    "causal_summary": "The review surfaced 91 P2 findings. None is a shipped runtime defect on a default-on path, but they are not uniform: some are cheap default-off-contract guards worth fixing before release, some are latent injection seams that are safe only while inputs stay constrained, and many are missing-assertion gaps on default-off features whose blast radius is low. Shipping a flat list invites either over-fixing low-value items or silently dropping ones that matter. The packet needs a single triaged view that says, per finding family, whether to fix now or accept as is, with the reason recorded.",
